  , the square root 
  
    
      
        
          
            S
          
        
        =
        
          
            a
          
        
        ×
        
          2
          
            n
          
        
      
    
    {\displaystyle {\sqrt {S}}={\sqrt {a}}\times 2^{n}}
   can be estimated as 

  
    
      
        
          
            S
          
        
        ≈
        (
        0.485
        +
        0.485
        ⋅
        a
        )
        ⋅
        
          2
          
            n
          
        
      
    
    {\displaystyle {\sqrt {S}}\approx (0.485+0.485\cdot a)\cdot 2^{n}}
  which is the least-squares regression line to 3 significant digit coefficients. 
  
    
      
        
          
            a
          
        
      
    
    {\displaystyle {\sqrt {a}}}
   has maximum absolute error of 0.0408 at 
  
    
      
        a
      
    
    {\displaystyle a}
  =2, and maximum relative error of 3.0% at 
  
    
      
        a
      
    
    {\displaystyle a}
  =1.  A computationally convenient rounded estimate (because the coefficients are powers of 2) is:

  
    
      
        
          
